01:01.253 --> 01:31.193
living turning the soil, and we had animals, and we 
respected the animals. The animals worked for us,

01:36.255 --> 01:41.063
and if we cared for the animals, they'd do the work 
for us. They were important to us, and we had them to

01:43.226 --> 01:46.110
eat. We had hogs, and we killed hogs, and we killed 
calves, and all that, and we ate them. Right over

01:50.617 --> 01:55.445
the farm, we didn't go out and buy the reef or the 
port. That was produced right there on the farm.

01:58.770 --> 01:59.391
And, uh, Animals were very important out there. 
And there was a need for the care of those animals.

02:08.093 --> 02:15.159
The veterinarian's lifestyle then was 
individual animal treatment. Pure and simple.

02:16.240 --> 02:22.846
The old cow got sick and he was called to treat the 
old cow.

02:24.627 --> 02:26.769
The dog wasn't as fortunate. He could go. didn't 
even call the veterinarian for a dog or take him to

02:30.320 --> 02:33.805
the veterinarian either. But the dog was an 
essential utilitarian animal around the place,

02:34.807 --> 02:40.917
but you can get more dogs very fast. And so he wasn't 
as important. Oh, he had his pets, yeah, but mostly

02:45.344 --> 02:49.610
they were utilitarian. They didn't come in the 
house, and we didn't pet them like we do today, but I

02:49.630 --> 02:55.720
had a little dog. that I thought the world of when I 
was a kid, the little squirrel dogs and things. I

03:01.094 --> 03:01.915
found a lot of squirrels. Highly utilitarian. You 
bet. And sheepdogs and all those, you know, that

03:07.021 --> 03:12.026
handle little goats and herd them. But the dog was a 
dog and not a people and they had no rights. But we

03:21.036 --> 03:22.858
treated them nicely. We fed them carefully. and 
gave them a good place to sleep and all that. Tried

03:28.685 --> 03:31.748
to treat them right. And as a kid, we were taught 
that. Well, people began to move to the town. You

03:41.516 --> 03:51.604
know, urbanization took place, and country 
people moved to town, and country people had been

03:41.516 --> 03:51.604
related to animals out there in the country. And 
they got into the town, concrete jungles, and

03:54.948 --> 04:00.735
those animals weren't there, and they missed 
those animals. They longed for those animals. So

04:03.098 --> 04:06.683
they began slowly to take in pets. Now these are 
really pets then, you see. They're not really

04:10.407 --> 04:13.591
utilitarian, but they're pets. They're 
satisfying the emotions of people rather than the

04:13.611 --> 04:19.418
economics of people. So it went from economics to 
emotional. And pets now are emotional

04:23.281 --> 04:30.713
characters.

